<p>Hi! I’m a Ph.D. student in the <a href="https://linguistics.cornell.edu">Linguistics department</a> at Cornell University working with <a href="https://vansky.github.io">Marten van Schijndel</a> and <a href="https://linguistics.cornell.edu/helena-aparicio">Helena Aparicio</a>.</p>

<p>I study how our minds work on language processing, which always makes me an excited language nerd.</p>

<p>My main research areas are in human sentence processing and experimental pragmatics, but I’m also very interested in applying formal methods from statistics and computational modelling/NLP into human language processing.</p>

<p>And I’m a visiting researcher at Brain and Cognition Research Center at Konkuk University, where I finished my Masters on Korean psycholinguistics with prof. Upyong Hong (홍우평) and prof. Yunju Nam (남윤주).</p>

<p>Other than these, I’m a <a href="/assets/img/lefty.png">lefty</a>, and a (right-handed) <a href="/assets/img/me_guitarist.png">guitarist</a>.</p>
